The candidate lists generated for popular subjects tend to have higher precision and recall. For instance, F1 score for (state, borders) with top-{{arxiv_2307_03122_FO0024||FO}} is the lowest due to the presence of long-tail subjects. Also for a large possible set of valid objects, e.g., in occupation, LM only generates common professions with a high probability and negatively impacts the F1 scores. This behavior, however, helps in language type relations. A similar difference in performance can be observed in [shin-etal-2020-autoprompt, zhong-etal-2021-factual].